wikipedia_page.main: Lois Rosindale (born 17 April 1990 in Leeds) is an English professional triathlete, 2011 British Champion, and 2010 U23 Duathlon Vice World Champion. Rosindale is a member of the High Performance Triathlon Squad based in Leeds.
